# Theory

## What are Props in React?

Props is short for **Properties**.

Props are used to pass data from one React component to another component.

Props generally allow data to be passed from a **parent component** to a **child component**.

For example, if a parent component wants to send a name to a child component, it can pass the name as a prop.

